      "title": "\u2600\ufe0f Solar Audification Study",
      "bodyHtml": "<p>Your task is to listen to magnetometer data from the&nbsp;<b>GOES satellite</b>&nbsp;and identify&nbsp;<b>Electromagnetic Ion Cyclotron (EMIC) waves</b>. This study should take approximately 20-30 minutes.</p><p><br></p><p>Please use headphones or high-quality speakers in a quiet environment free from distractions. Listen carefully and draw boxes around any features you identify in the spectrogram, and when you are finished use the \"Complete\" button to submit your results.</p><p><br></p><hr><p><br></p><p>If you have any questions or need assistance, please contact the CHIRP team at <a href=\"mailto:chirpscienceproject@gmail.com\">chirpscienceproject@gmail.com</a>.</p>",
